getRootFolder

IFolderHandle getRootFolder()
Returns the root folder of this component.

The party that initially creates the component's root folder (in some workspace) is responsible for recording it with the component.

TODO Issue: In the world of siloed components, the root folder for a component exists in the initial configuration. If two parties each add the same new component to separate workspaces (in separate repos) using addComponent(IComponent), we need to ensure that they both end up with the same root folder item. Otherwise, the two components will never be commensurable, and change sets that work for one may not work for the other. The solution is to assign a root folder item id at component creation time; i.e., in the implementation of IItemFactory.createComponent(IAudtiable,String), or, better still, in the EMF factory method so that we can initialize components created by IItemFactory.createAuditable.

Returns:
this component's root folder, or null if none

getInitialBaseline

IBaselineHandle getInitialBaseline()
Returns the initial baseline of this component. The configuration of the initial baseline contains only the (empty) root folder. The initial baseline is created when the Component is created (using IWorkspaceManager.createComponent).

Returns:
handle of the initial baseline value of the component (will not be null)
